text: Gundula "Gundi" Busch (April 29, 1935 â€“ January 31, 2014) was a German figure skater. Busch was born in Milan, Italy. She was the 1954 World champion, the 1954 European champion, and a two-time West German national champion. She also was part of the 1952 Winter Olympics. Busch died on January 31, 2021 in Stockholm, Sweden at the age of 78. ==References== Category:1935 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Olympians for Germany Category:German figure skaters Category:Sportspeople from Milan
